snippet: The authorities met no resistance, with student protesters saying they would not oppose a court order to remove barricades around a tower near government headquarters.
abstract: Hong Kong government sends police to clear pro-democracy protesters from small area in front of office building in first move against demonstrators in weeks; authorities meet no resistance, with student protesters saying they will not oppose court order.

byline.original: By CHRIS BUCKLEY and ALAN WONG
byline.contributor: Keith Bradsher and Michael Forsythe contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: The authorities met no resistance, with student protesters saying they would not oppose a court order to remove barricades around a tower near government headquarters.

headline.main: Hong Kong Clears an Area of Pro-Democracy Protesters
headline.print_headline: Hong Kong Clears an Area of Pro-Democracy Protesters
